description.narrative: Access to water and sanitation was improved in several PICTs. In Vanuatu, access to safe drinking water improved for 1,000 people in highest risk communities, and nearly 2,000 children from 101 early childhood care and education (ECCE) centres in Penama Province benefitted from improved water and sanitation facilities. An innovative and low-cost foot-operated handwashing station was introduced to improve access for children with disabilities in a school in Fiji. In Kiribati, WASH facilities in five healthcare facilities were improved through infrastructure installation/upgrades and capacity building. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
